---
import Article from '../layouts/Article.astro';

const title = 'Supported devices — what FunGen drives (Handy, OSR2/SR6, Buttplug)';
const description =
  'The hardware FunGen plays funscripts to: The Handy, Autoblow, Vacuglide, the OSR2/SR6/SSR1 over T-Code, and anything on Buttplug.io / Intiface — with latency compensation.';
const canonicalPath = '/supported-devices';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');

const articleLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  headline: 'Devices FunGen supports',
  description,
  inLanguage: 'en',
  mainEntityOfPage: 'https://fungen.app/supported-devices',
  author: { '@type': 'Organization', name: 'FunGen' },
  publisher: {
    '@type': 'Organization',
    name: 'FunGen',
    logo: { '@type': 'ImageObject', url: 'https://fungen.app/icon-512.png' },
  },
};
const breadcrumbs = [{ name: 'Supported devices', path: '/supported-devices' }];
---

<Article
  {title}
  {description}
  heading="Devices FunGen supports"
  {canonicalPath}
  {articleLd}
  {breadcrumbs}
>
  <p class="lead">
    FunGen plays <a href={`${base}/what-is-a-funscript`}>funscripts</a> straight to your hardware,
    with per-device interpolation and latency compensation so the motion stays in time with the
    video. It works with the gear you already have:
  </p>

  <h2>The Handy</h2>
  <p>
    Connect over <strong>HTTPS (Handy Connect API)</strong> or <strong>Bluetooth LE</strong>, with
    latency compensation tuned for the Handy's round-trip. Generate a stroke script for any 2D or VR
    video and play it from the couch or a headset.
    <a href={`${base}/funscripts-for-the-handy`}>More on FunGen + The Handy →</a>
  </p>

  <h2>OSR2 / SR6 / SSR1</h2>
  <p>
    The T-Code builds are where <strong>multi-axis</strong> shines. FunGen's AI writes stroke plus
    roll, pitch and twist, and routes each axis to your device so you get full motion, not just a
    piston. <a href={`${base}/funscripts-for-osr2-sr6`}>More on FunGen + OSR2 / SR6 →</a>
  </p>

  <h2>Autoblow</h2>
  <p>
    Drive the <strong>Autoblow Ultra</strong> from its stroke track. Generate the script with AI,
    refine it on the timeline, and play it in sync — the same one-app workflow as every other device.
  </p>

  <h2>Vacuglide</h2>
  <p>
    FunGen supports the <strong>Vacuglide</strong> directly, so a generated or hand-built script
    drives it with the same interpolation and latency handling as the rest.
  </p>

  <h2>Buttplug.io / Intiface</h2>
  <p>
    Beyond the built-in integrations, FunGen speaks to <strong>Buttplug.io / Intiface</strong> — the
    open bridge to a long list of consumer toys. If your device works with Intiface, FunGen can drive
    it from a funscript, which makes it a practical
    <a href={`${base}/funscript-editor`}>funscript editor and player</a> for hardware it doesn't
    integrate with natively.
  </p>

  <h2>How devices stay in sync</h2>
  <p>
    Whatever the device, FunGen applies <strong>per-device interpolation</strong> (smoothing the
    motion to what the hardware can do) and <strong>latency compensation</strong> (so the action
    lands on the beat). A built-in streamer can drive a session from a phone or VR headset while the
    device follows, and the <strong>Funscript Doctor</strong> scores a script against your specific
    device's limits before you play it.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a href={`${base}/`}>Download FunGen</a> and play to the device you already own — free to try.
  </p>
</Article>
